<docs>
	<doc for="XmlNodeChangedEventHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that handles
 <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeChanged"/>, <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeChanging"/>, <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeInserted"/>, <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeInserting"/>, <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeRemoved"/> and <see cref="System.Xml.XmlDocument.NodeRemoving"/> events.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="sender">The source of the event.</param>
		<param name=" e">An <see cref="System.Xml.XmlNodeChangedEventArgs"/> containing the event data.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>When you create
 an <see langword="XmlNodeChangedEventHandler"/> delegate, you identify
 the method that handles the event. To associate the event with your event
 handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The event handler is
 called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more
 information about event handler delegates, see <see topic="cpconEventsDelegates"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
 The following example shows how to handle the <see langword="NodeChanged"/>
 and <see langword="NodeInserted"/> events.
<codelink SampleID="XmlNodeChangedEventHandler" SnippetID="1"/>

The example uses the file, <see langword="book.xml"/>, as input.
 

<codelink SampleID="XmlNodeChangedEventHandler" SnippetID="2"/>
		</example>
	</doc></docs>
